item_name: Total Tax and Loan Note Accounts Table V
description: This line item is no longer in use. The Treasury Tax and Loan (TT&L) account summarized in Table V was the program through which Treasury invested its short term excess cash with outside banks until November 2008 when the program was suspended. Treasury subsequently decommissioned the legacy TT&L system through which investments were made.  In the beginning of October 2012, the program was renamed to 'Short Term Cash Investments,' which is the current name for Table V and related line items. Both names represent Treasury‰Ûªs short term cash investments (i.e. short term extra cash invested with external counterparties).
